text.tspan: Climate change: change of mass of US glaciers
Cumulative mass balance of U.S. reference glaciers, relative to the base year 1965.
This is given in meters of water equivalent, which represent changes in the average thickness of a glacier.
Source: US Geological Survey via the United States Environmental Protection Agency (EPA)
